INSERT INTO public.sample_essays VALUES ('740b3683-04cb-440b-8fee-ca53ceb0899b', '[FORECAST SPEAKING] Dự Đoán IELTS SPEAKING TUẦN (25/5-31/5)', 'forecast-speaking-du-doan-ielts-speaking-tuan-255-315', '<h1 dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">FORECAST SPEAKING 25/5 -31/5</h1>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Lưu ý: đây chỉ là những đề có xu hướng được hỏi nhiều trong phòng thi, sau khi ôn những đề này vẫn cần ôn các đề còn lại trong forecast</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Sử dụng <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-NfjggXjSs-ielts-prediction-ai">Chat Bot</a> để luyện tập tại nhà </p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>PDF </strong>tải<strong> </strong><span style="color: #3598db;"><a style="color: #3598db;" href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1BpLS_S8kcQ_6Yw727sODX0MuTij6B2yY/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TẠI ĐÂY</a></span></span></p>
<div dir="ltr" align="left">
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 1px; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col width="248"><col width="379"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px;">
<p dir="ltr">Part One</p>
<br>
<p dir="ltr">Where you live</p>
<br>
<p dir="ltr">Work/study</p>
<br>
<ol>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Park and gardens.</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Music </p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Shopping</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Morning routine</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Buildings</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Science</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Jokes &amp; Comedies</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Cars</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Headphones</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Teachers</p>
</li>
</ol>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px;">
<p dir="ltr">Part Two/Three</p>
<br>
<ol>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe an ambition that you haven’t achieved</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe your favorite city that you have visited</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe a time when you gave advice to others</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe a home that you like to visit but do not want to live in</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe an important decision that you made </p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe a person who makes plans a lot and is good at planning</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe an interesting video. </p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe an advertisement with a famous person in it</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation"> Describe a live sports event you watched and liked</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Describe a time when you worked in a group</p>
</li>
</ol>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Examiner to ask questions from EITHER Frame 1 or Frame 2</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 1 (Where you live now)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about where you live now</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which town or city do you live in now?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are there any things you don’t like about your area? (What are they?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you think you will continue to live there for a long time? (Why? Why not?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What are some changes in the area recently?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you live in a house or an apartment?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What is your favourite room in your home? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What things make your home pleasant to live in? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are the people in your neighbourhood nice and friendly?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you know any of your neighbours?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Is the place where you live quiet or noisy?</p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 2 (Work/ Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about what you do. Do you work or are you a student?</p>
<p dir="ltr">(Work)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What kind of work do you do?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you – the people you work with or the work you do? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you work best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Would you like to change the place you work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">(Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your studies? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you—the teachers or the other students on your course? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How much time do you spend studying every week?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How do you usually travel to the city where you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you study best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Have you always wanted to study this subject/ these subjects (Why/ Why not?)</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;">1 Park and gardens</span></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Did you like going to parks as a child?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. I used to go to parks quite a lot when I was a kid, especially on weekends with my family. I mean, parks were probably one of the few places where I could run around freely, play games, and hang out with my friends. Looking back, those trips were actually a big part of my childhood.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Do you still like going to parks now?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Yeah, I do, although I go there for different reasons now. These days, I usually visit parks when I need a break from studying or work because they’re much quieter and less stressful than crowded places. Sometimes I just take a walk, listen to music, or simply sit there to clear my mind.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Would you like to see more parks in your city?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Absolutely. I think more parks would really improve people’s quality of life, especially in big cities where there’s a lot of traffic and pollution. Parks provide green spaces where people can exercise, relax, or spend time with their families. Plus, they make the city look much more livable and attractive.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Are there any parks you want to go to in the future?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, yeah, definitely. I’d love to visit some famous national parks abroad, especially places with amazing scenery and wildlife. For example, I’ve always wanted to see places like Yellowstone or Banff because, you know, they look incredibly peaceful and breathtaking in photos and videos.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>2 Music</strong></span> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1 Do you prefer sad or happy music?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, I’d say I generally prefer happy music. It just puts me in a better mood and helps me relax after a long day. That said, sometimes I do listen to sad songs, especially when I want to, you know, unwind or reflect on things a bit.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2 Does happy music make you feel more excited?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. I mean, happy music usually has a faster rhythm, so it naturally lifts my mood and gives me more energy. Sometimes, when I feel tired, I just put on some upbeat songs, and it really helps me feel more motivated.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3 Have you taken any music classes?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, actually I have. When I was a kid, my parents enrolled me in a piano class for around two years. To be honest, I wasn’t really good at it, but I enjoyed learning some basic songs and, you know, practicing with my friends. I guess it was a fun experience overall, even though I don’t play the piano anymore.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4 Do you listen to music while doing other things?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Oh yes, all the time, actually. I usually listen to music while studying, cleaning the house, or even working out. I mean, music helps me feel more relaxed and less bored. But, well, if I’m doing something that requires a lot of concentration, I tend to choose instrumental music because songs with lyrics can be a bit distracting sometimes.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8; font-size: 14pt;"><strong>3 Shopping</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. How often do you go shopping?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, I’d say I go shopping quite regularly, probably once or twice a week. Most of the time, I just buy daily necessities like food or skincare products. But occasionally, I also shop for clothes or other things when I need them.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Do you prefer online shopping or in-store shopping?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I probably prefer online shopping because it’s much more convenient and saves a lot of time. I mean, I can easily compare prices and order things without leaving my house. That said, for clothes or shoes, I still prefer shopping in-store so I can try them on first.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Have you ever returned anything you bought online?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, I have, actually. Once I ordered a shirt online, but when it arrived, the size was completely different from what I expected. So I ended up returning it and getting a refund. Luckily, the process was pretty straightforward.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do you like shopping?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, I do, to some extent. I think shopping can be enjoyable, especially when I’m buying something I really like. But honestly, I’m not the type of person who spends hours shopping because it can get tiring after a while.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>4 Morning time</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you like getting up early in the morning?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">To be honest, not really. I’m more of a night owl, so waking up early is a bit of a struggle for me. But when I do manage to get up early, I actually enjoy the peaceful atmosphere — everything feels calm and quiet, which is quite refreshing.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. What do you usually do in the morning?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, on weekdays, I usually start my day by washing my face, brushing my teeth, and making a cup of tea or coffee. Then I check my to-do list and begin studying or working, depending on the day. I try to avoid checking social media right away, just to stay focused.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What did you do in the morning when you were little? Why?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">When I was a kid, my morning routine was pretty simple. I’d wake up, get dressed in my school uniform, and have breakfast — usually bánh mì or a bowl of phở. My mom always made sure I had a full stomach before heading to school. Back then, everything was very routine and guided by my parents.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Are there any differences between what you do in the morning now and what you did in the past?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yes, definitely. In the past, my mornings were quite passive — I just followed whatever my parents told me to do. But now, I have more control over my schedule. I plan my mornings around productivity, like doing revision or checking emails. It’s more structured, but also more flexible in a way.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5. Do you spend your mornings doing the same things on both weekends and weekdays? Why?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Not really. On weekdays, my mornings are quite rushed because I have classes or work to get to. But on weekends, I allow myself to sleep in a bit and take things slow. I might cook something nice for breakfast or go out for a coffee with friends. It’s my way of recharging after a hectic week.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>5 Building</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Are there tall buildings near your home?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yes, quite a few actually. I live in a fairly urbanized area, so the skyline is dotted with high-rise apartment blocks and commercial towers. One of the tallest buildings nearby is a modern office complex that really stands out because of its glass facade. It''s quite impressive, especially at night when it''s fully lit.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Do you take photos of buildings?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Occasionally, yes. I’m particularly drawn to buildings with unique or historic architecture. When I travel, I often find myself photographing cathedrals, temples, or even old colonial structures—anything that has character or tells a story. It’s not just about aesthetics, but also capturing cultural heritage.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Is there a building that you would like to visit?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Definitely! I’ve always wanted to visit the Sydney Opera House. Its design is so iconic and futuristic, and I think it would be fascinating to see it in person. Not just from the outside, but I’d love to attend a performance there too, to really soak in the atmosphere.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do you want to live in a tall building?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">To be honest, I wouldn’t mind it. Living on a high floor often comes with spectacular views and a quieter environment, away from the street noise. But at the same time, I’d be concerned about things like elevator breakdowns or feeling a bit isolated. So I guess it would depend on the design and location of the building.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>6 Science</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you like science?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, I do, to some extent. I mean, science helps us understand how the world works, which I find pretty fascinating. Although I’m not really into complicated theories, I still enjoy learning about topics related to space or technology.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. When did you start to learn about science?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, I think I started learning science in primary school. At first, it was just simple things like plants, animals, or basic experiments. But as I got older, the subjects became more detailed and interesting.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Which science subject is interesting to you?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I’d say astronomy is probably the most interesting one for me. I’ve always been curious about space, planets, and, you know, the possibility of life on other planets. I think it’s amazing how much scientists have discovered about the universe.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. What kinds of interesting things have you done with science?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, back in school, I remember doing some simple science experiments in class, like mixing chemicals or building small electric circuits. They were actually quite fun because we got to learn things in a more practical way instead of just reading textbooks.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5. Do you like watching science TV programs?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, sometimes I do. I especially enjoy documentaries about space or new technology because they’re both educational and entertaining. Plus, I think visual programs make scientific topics much easier to understand.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>7 Jokes &amp; Comedies</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>1. Are comedy shows popular in your country?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, for sure. Comedy shows are pretty popular in my country, especially among young people. I mean, after a long day of work or studying, people just want something light and entertaining to watch. These days, short comedy clips on TikTok or YouTube are everywhere.</p>
<p><strong>2. Are you good at telling jokes?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Umm… not really, to be honest . I’m more like the person who laughs at jokes instead of telling them. Sometimes I try to be funny, but yeah… the joke usually sounds better in my head than in real life.</p>
<p><strong>3. Do your friends like to tell jokes?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. Some of my friends are super funny and always joke around when we hang out. They can literally make everyone laugh, even in awkward situations, so being around them is really enjoyable.</p>
<p><strong>4. Do you like to watch comedies?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Oh yes, absolutely. I’m really into comedies because they help me relax and forget about stress for a while. I especially enjoy sitcoms and movies with natural humor instead of over-the-top jokes.</p>
<p><strong>5. Have you ever watched a live show?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, I have, actually. I went to a live comedy show with a couple of friends last year, and it was such a fun experience. The atmosphere was amazing because everyone was laughing together, and it felt much more exciting than watching online.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>8 Cars</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you think car colours are important?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Yeah, I think they are, to some extent. I mean, the colour of a car can reflect a person’s personality or style. For example, some people prefer black or white cars because they look elegant, while others choose brighter colours to stand out.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Did you enjoy traveling by car when you were a kid?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Yeah, definitely. I used to enjoy road trips with my family when I was younger. I mean, even though long journeys could be a bit tiring sometimes, I still liked looking out the window and listening to music during the trip.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What types of cars do you like?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> I’d say I prefer modern and practical cars, especially SUVs. They usually have more space and are more comfortable for long trips. Plus, I really like cars with advanced technology and safety features.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do you prefer to be a driver or a passenger?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Hmm, I’d rather be a passenger, to be honest. I mean, when I’m a passenger, I can just relax, listen to music, or look at my phone instead of focusing on the road. Driving can be quite stressful, especially in heavy traffic.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5. What do you usually do when there is a traffic jam?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Well, if I’m stuck in traffic, I usually listen to music or scroll through my phone if I’m not driving. But honestly, traffic jams can be really frustrating, especially when I’m in a hurry or running late.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>9 Headphones</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you use headphones?</strong><br>Yeah, I do, pretty much every day. I usually use them when I’m listening to music, watching videos, or studying in noisy places. I mean, headphones help me focus better and avoid distractions.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. In what conditions would you not use headphones?</strong><br>Hmm, probably when I’m walking on busy streets or crossing the road because it can be dangerous if I can’t hear what’s happening around me. I also avoid using them when talking to other people since it might seem a bit rude.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. When would you use headphones?</strong><br>I mostly use them when I’m studying, working out, or travelling on public transport. Sometimes I also put them on when I just want to relax and enjoy some music without disturbing other people.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. What type of headphones do you use?</strong><br>I currently use wireless earbuds because they’re really convenient and easy to carry around. Plus, I don’t have to deal with tangled wires, which is honestly one of the things I hated about traditional headphones.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr"> </h2>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>10 Teachers</strong></span> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1 Do you have a favorite teacher?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, I do. My favourite was my English teacher in high school. She was really friendly and approachable, so I felt comfortable asking questions. Also, her lessons were quite engaging, which made me enjoy learning more.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2 Do you want to be a teacher in the future?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, probably not, to be honest. I mean, teaching is a very meaningful job, but it can also be quite demanding. You need a lot of patience and responsibility, which I’m not sure I have. So I think I’ll choose a different career path.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3 Do you have a teacher from your past that you still remember?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. I still remember my primary school teacher quite clearly. She was very kind and patient, especially with young students like us. She also helped me out a lot when I had difficulties with my studies.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4 Are you still in touch with your primary school teachers?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Not really. It’s been a long time, so we’ve kind of lost touch. But I still remember them and the things they taught me. I’m actually quite grateful for the foundation they gave me</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5 In what way has your favourite teacher helped you?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I’d say she helped me become more confident, especially in speaking English. She always encouraged me to speak up in class, even when I wasn’t sure about my answers. She also gave useful feedback, which really helped me improve over time.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>1 Describe an ambition that you haven’t achieved</strong></span><br>You should say:</p>
<ul>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">What it is</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Why you haven’t achieved it</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">What you are doing about it now</p>
</li>
<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">
<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">And how you feel about it</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p dir="ltr">One ambition I haven’t achieved yet is getting an IELTS Band 7. I’ve been studying for the IELTS exam for a while, but reaching that score has been challenging for me. I need Band 7 for my study plans, so it’s a goal I really want to accomplish.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The main reason I haven’t achieved it yet is because of certain areas that I find difficult, like speaking and writing. Even though I’ve gone over the rules and techniques, I still struggle with expressing myself clearly in writing, and sometimes I feel nervous during the speaking test, which holds me back from doing my best. There’s also the pressure to get everything right, which makes it harder to stay calm and focused.</p>
<p dir="ltr">To work toward this goal, I’m taking extra classes and practicing regularly. I’m going through sample tests and focusing on areas where I need improvement, like writing more complex sentences and speaking naturally. I also watch videos and listen to podcasts to pick up new vocabulary and expressions that can help me in both writing and speaking.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I feel determined to keep at it because I know how important this score is for my future. Although it’s tough, I’m confident that with consistent practice, I’ll get there. It’s a challenging goal, but I’m motivated to put in the effort and achieve it someday soo</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. What ambitions do children usually have?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Children often dream of becoming doctors, astronauts, teachers, or athletes because they find these jobs exciting and inspiring. Many are influenced by movies, books, or role models and choose ambitions based on what they admire.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Why are some people very ambitious in their work?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Some people are ambitious because they want success, financial stability, or personal growth. Others are naturally driven and competitive, always seeking higher positions and new challenges. Ambition is often influenced by upbringing and environment.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Why don’t some people have dreams?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Some people lack dreams because they are content with their current life or lack motivation due to personal struggles. Others may have faced failures or discouragement, making them hesitant to set big goals. Sometimes, a lack of exposure to opportunities also limits ambition.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. How do people balance work and life?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">People balance work and life by setting clear priorities, managing time effectively, and making time for family and hobbies. Some practice work-life balance strategies like avoiding overtime, exercising regularly, or taking breaks to reduce stress.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>2 Describe your favorite city that you have visited</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Where it is</p>
<p dir="ltr">How you knew it </p>
<p dir="ltr">When you visited it</p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why it is your favourite city </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about Da Nang, which is probably my favorite city that I’ve ever visited.</p>
<p dir="ltr">It’s a coastal city in central Vietnam, and I first knew about it through social media and recommendations from my friends. I’d seen a lot of photos and videos of its beaches, modern bridges, and local food, so I really wanted to visit it someday.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I went there about two years ago with a few close friends during a summer holiday. We stayed there for around four days and visited many famous places like My Khe Beach, Ba Na Hills, and the Dragon Bridge. We also tried a lot of local dishes, which was honestly one of the best parts of the trip.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The reason why Da Nang became my favorite city is that it has a really nice balance between modern life and nature. The city is clean, less crowded than some other big cities, and the people there were very friendly. Also, the atmosphere felt much more relaxing and peaceful, which helped me forget about stress for a while.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, even though I’ve visited a few different places, Da Nang is still the city that left the strongest impression on me, and I’d definitely love to go back there in the future.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Which is more suitable for young people, urban life or rural life, and which is more suitable for old people?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I think urban life is generally more suitable for young people because cities usually offer better job opportunities, education, and entertainment. Young people often enjoy the fast-paced lifestyle and modern facilities. On the other hand, rural areas might be better for older people since the environment is quieter, less stressful, and has cleaner air.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. How do people choose a city to travel to?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think people usually choose a destination based on their interests and budget. For example, some people prefer cities with beautiful scenery or historical attractions, while others look for good food or shopping opportunities. Nowadays, social media and travel reviews also influence people a lot when deciding where to go.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Do you think a tourist city is also a good place to live? Why?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, it depends. Tourist cities are often lively and have good facilities, restaurants, and entertainment, which can make life more convenient and exciting. However, they can also be crowded and expensive because there are so many visitors. So I think they’re great for some people, but not for everyone.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do most people prefer traveling to a modern city or a historical city?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, I think it really depends on personal preference. Younger travelers might prefer modern cities because they enjoy shopping malls, nightlife, and technology. Meanwhile, other people may prefer historical cities because they want to learn about culture and history. Personally, I think many tourists enjoy a mix of both.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>3 Describe a time when you gave advice to others</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">When it was</p>
<p dir="ltr">To whom you gave the advice</p>
<p dir="ltr">What the advice was</p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why you gave the advice</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I remember a time about six months ago when I gave some advice to one of my classmates. She was preparing for the IELTS exam, and to be honest, she was really stressed out — especially about the Writing section. She kept telling me she had no idea how to organize her ideas or how to use academic vocabulary properly.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, during one of our study sessions, she asked me for some tips. I told her, you know, the first thing she should do is read model essays to understand the structure — like how to write clear topic sentences, use cohesive devices, and stay on topic. I also recommended that she keep a vocabulary journal to collect useful phrases and collocations. Actually, I shared some of my own writing samples with her and showed her how I planned my essays using outlines.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The reason I gave her this advice was because I had already taken the test and got a decent score, so I knew what worked for me. Plus, I just wanted to help her feel more confident and less overwhelmed. In the end, she followed the advice, and a few weeks later, she told me she scored 7.0 in Writing, which made me feel really proud and happy for her.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Should people prepare before giving advice?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">"Well, let me see... I’d say yes, definitely. Giving advice is actually a pretty big responsibility, so you shouldn''t just say the first thing that comes to mind, you know? It’s much better to think it over and really consider the other person''s situation first. I mean, if you''re too rushed, your advice might actually make things worse instead of helping them out."</p>
<p><strong>2. Is it good to ask advice from strangers online?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">"To be honest, it’s a bit of a mixed bag. I mean, on one hand, you can get different points of view from people all over the world, which is great. But on the other hand, there’s so much fake information on the internet these days. So, I guess it’s fine for small things like tech tips, but for serious life decisions, you should be really careful about who you trust."</p>
<p><strong>3. What are the personalities of people whose job is to give advice?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">"That’s an interesting question. I’d say they need two main traits. First of all, they must be great listeners—you can''t really help someone if you don''t understand them, right? And secondly, they should be open-minded. If they are too judgmental, people will just feel uncomfortable and won''t want to share their problems with them anymore."</p>
<p><strong>4. What are the problems if you ask too many people for advice?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">"The biggest issue, I think, is that you just end up getting super confused. When you hear too many conflicting opinions, it becomes almost impossible to make a final choice. It’s like, you lose your own voice and end up feeling even more stressed than when you started. It’s basically a case of ''too many cooks in the kitchen''."</p>
<p><strong>5. Why do some people think it is better to ask for advice from friends than from parents?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">"I think it mostly boils down to the fact that friends are closer to our age. They’re usually going through the same struggles, so their advice feels more relatable. With parents, you know, sometimes there’s a fear of being judged, or we might feel their advice is a bit old-fashioned and doesn''t quite fit today''s world."</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>4 Describe a home that you like to visit but do not want to live in</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Where it is</p>
<p dir="ltr">What it is like</p>
<p dir="ltr">Why you like to visit it</p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why you would not like to live there </p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about my cousin’s house, which is a place I really enjoy visiting but probably wouldn’t want to live in permanently.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Her house is located in a small countryside area, about two hours away from my city. It’s a large traditional house with a beautiful garden, and the atmosphere there is really peaceful and relaxing. There are lots of trees, flowers, and open spaces around the house, so it feels very close to nature.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I like visiting it because it’s a perfect place to take a break from busy city life. Whenever I go there, I feel much calmer and less stressed. Usually, I spend time chatting with my cousin, eating home-cooked meals, or just sitting outside enjoying the fresh air. Honestly, it’s the kind of place where you can truly relax.</p>
<p dir="ltr">However, I don’t think I’d like to live there long-term. The main reason is that it’s quite far from the city center, so it’s not very convenient. There aren’t many shopping centers, entertainment places, or public services nearby. Also, I think I’d eventually get bored because the lifestyle there is much quieter and slower than what I’m used to.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, even though I really enjoy visiting that house occasionally, I still prefer living in a more modern and convenient area.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do people in your country like to visit others’ homes?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. In my country, visiting other people’s homes is quite common, especially during holidays, birthdays, or special occasions. I mean, it’s considered a good way to maintain relationships and spend time with family or friends.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. What do people do when they visit others?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, people usually chat, eat together, or sometimes bring small gifts like fruit or snacks. If it’s a special occasion, they might also celebrate or have a meal together. Honestly, visiting someone’s house is often more about socializing and enjoying each other’s company.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What kind of place do people in your country like to live in?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think most people prefer living in places that are convenient and comfortable. For example, younger people often like modern apartments in the city because they’re close to work or entertainment areas, while older people may prefer quieter places with more space and greenery.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. What''s the difference between homes in cities and those in the countryside?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, there are quite a few differences. Homes in cities are usually smaller and more modern because space is limited and expensive. In contrast, countryside houses tend to be larger and surrounded by nature. Also, life in rural areas is generally quieter and less stressful than in big cities.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>5 Describe an important decision that you made</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:   </p>
<p dir="ltr">What the decision was  </p>
<p dir="ltr">How you made your decision  </p>
<p dir="ltr">What the results of the decision were    </p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why it was important </p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about an important decision that I made about two years ago, which was deciding to focus seriously on learning English and preparing for the IELTS exam.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Before making that decision, I spent quite a lot of time thinking about my future goals. I realized that improving my English could open up more opportunities for studying, working, and even travelling abroad. I also talked to my parents and some friends for advice before finally deciding to commit to it.</p>
<p dir="ltr">After making the decision, I started studying English more consistently. I joined an IELTS course, practiced speaking almost every day, and tried to spend more time watching videos and reading in English. Honestly, it wasn’t easy at first because balancing study and other responsibilities was quite stressful.</p>
<p dir="ltr">However, the results were really positive. My English improved a lot, especially my confidence in communication. I also became more disciplined and motivated because I had a clear goal to work toward.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I think it was an important decision because it changed my mindset and helped me develop useful skills for the future. Plus, learning English has given me access to more information and opportunities that I probably wouldn’t have had otherwise.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, looking back, I’m really glad that I made that decision.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you think children sometimes have to make important decisions?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. Even though children are still young, they sometimes have to make important decisions, especially about their studies or hobbies. For example, they may need to choose which subjects to focus on or what activities they want to join.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. What important decisions do teenagers need to make after graduation?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I think one of the biggest decisions is whether to continue studying or start working. They also need to decide what career path they want to pursue, which can have a huge impact on their future.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Who can children turn to for help when making a decision?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Usually, children ask their parents, teachers, or close friends for advice because these people have more experience and can give useful guidance. Nowadays, some young people also search for information online before making decisions.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do you think advertisements can influence our decisions when shopping?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yes, absolutely. Advertisements can strongly influence people because they often make products look more attractive or necessary than they really are. Social media advertising is especially powerful these days.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5. Do you think the influence of advertising is good?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think it can be both good and bad. On the positive side, advertisements help people discover useful products and services. However, some ads can be misleading and encourage people to buy things they don’t actually need.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>6 Describe a person who makes plans a lot and is good at planning</strong></span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who he/she is</p>
<p>How you knew him/her </p>
<p>What plans he/she makes </p>
<p>And explain how you feel about this person</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>SAMPLE</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, a person who’s really good at planning and makes detailed plans all the time is my older sister, Linh. She’s honestly one of the most organized people I’ve ever met.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I’ve, you know, known her my whole life, but I only started noticing how good she was at planning when we both reached high school. At that time, she was preparing for her university entrance exam, and she created this incredibly structured study schedule that she followed every single day. And the impressive thing is that she still plans like that for almost everything now — from her work tasks to her weekend activities.</p>
<p dir="ltr">She usually makes weekly and monthly plans, sets clear goals, and even breaks them down into smaller steps. For example, when she was studying for the IELTS exam, she planned exactly which skills to focus on each day and how many practice tests she would finish each week. And, well, she ended up getting a really high score, so her planning definitely paid off.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I feel genuinely inspired by her because she makes planning look so easy and, I mean, so effective. Whenever I’m feeling lost or overwhelmed, she always tells me to write things down and organize my thoughts, and it really helps. I admire her discipline and consistency, and I kinda hope I can become as structured as she is one day. So yeah, she’s the perfect example of someone who succeeds because she knows how to plan properly.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>PART 3</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Do you think it’s important to plan ahead?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yes, I think planning ahead is really important. It helps people stay organized and avoid unnecessary stress because, you know, they have a clearer idea of what needs to be done. Planning also saves time and prevents mistakes, especially in situations like studying or working. So even though not everything goes according to plan, having a direction is always useful.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Do you think children should plan their future careers?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I think children can explore ideas about their future, but they shouldn’t be pressured to make a fixed plan too early. Kids change their interests as they grow, so forcing them to choose a career might limit their creativity. It’s better to let them try different activities, understand their strengths, and then make a decision when they’re older and more self-aware.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Is making study plans popular among young people?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Actually, yes. Many young people these days make study plans because they want to manage their time more effectively, especially with exams and deadlines. You know, online tools and planners make it easier to organize tasks. However, not everyone sticks to the plan, so the real challenge is staying disciplined rather than just creating a plan.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Do you think choosing a college major is closely related to a person’s future career?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">In many cases, yes, but not always. For fields like medicine or engineering, the major directly determines the career path. But for other areas, people often end up working in completely different industries. I think what matters more is developing transferable skills, like communication or problem-solving, because careers nowadays are much more flexible than before.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>7 Describe an interesting video</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">When and where you watched it </p>
<p dir="ltr">What it is about </p>
<p dir="ltr">Why you watched it </p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain how you feel about it </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about an interesting video that I watched a few months ago on YouTube. It was actually an English-learning video that focused on improving speaking skills and pronunciation.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I watched it at home one evening while I was preparing for my IELTS exam. The video was made by an English teacher who explained how to sound more natural in conversations, especially by using linking words, filler words, and common expressions used by native speakers.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I decided to watch it because I wanted to improve my fluency and sound less robotic when speaking English. Also, a friend of mine recommended the channel to me, so I thought I’d give it a try.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Honestly, I found the video really helpful and engaging. The teacher explained things in a simple and entertaining way, so it wasn’t boring at all. After watching it, I actually learned a lot of useful expressions that I could apply in daily conversations and IELTS Speaking practice.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, I think it’s one of the most useful videos I’ve watched recently because it not only improved my English but also motivated me to practice more consistently.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. What kind of videos do people in your country like to watch?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, people in my country watch all kinds of videos, but I think entertainment content is probably the most popular. For example, many people enjoy short videos on TikTok, comedy clips, music videos, and travel vlogs. Educational videos and podcasts have also become more popular recently, especially among young people.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Which is more helpful, watching videos or reading books?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think both are useful in different ways. Watching videos can be more engaging and easier to understand because people can learn through visuals and sound. However, reading books usually helps people concentrate better and develop deeper knowledge. Personally, I think combining both methods is probably the best approach.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What skills can people learn from watching videos?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, quite a lot actually. People can learn practical skills like cooking, photography, language learning, or even computer skills through online videos. Also, motivational or educational content can help improve communication and problem-solving skills as well.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Are there any differences between the videos that young people and old people like to watch?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. Young people usually prefer fast-paced and entertaining content like vlogs, gaming videos, or social media clips. In contrast, older people tend to watch news programs, documentaries, or videos related to health and daily life. I think the difference mainly comes from their interests and lifestyles.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>8 Describe an advertisement with a famous person in it</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Who the person is</p>
<p dir="ltr">Where you can see it </p>
<p dir="ltr">What the advertisement is about</p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain how you feel about the advertisement </p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sanmple</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about an advertisement featuring a famous football player, Cristiano Ronaldo, which I saw quite a lot on YouTube and social media.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The advertisement was for a sports brand, and it mainly promoted sportswear and running shoes. In the video, Ronaldo was shown training hard, working out, and encouraging people to stay active and never give up on their goals.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I first saw this advertisement online a few months ago, and since Ronaldo is such a well-known athlete, it immediately caught my attention. I mean, even people who aren’t football fans probably know who he is.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Honestly, I really liked the advertisement because it felt inspiring and energetic rather than just trying to sell a product. The background music, visuals, and motivational message made it really memorable. Also, I think using a famous athlete was a smart idea because people tend to trust products more when they’re promoted by someone successful and influential.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Another reason I liked it is that it actually motivated me to exercise more and pay attention to my health. So yeah, compared to many other advertisements, this one left quite a strong impression on me.</p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. What are the advantages and disadvantages of advertisements?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Well, advertisements have both positive and negative sides. On the positive side, they help people learn about new products, services, and special offers. They’re also important for businesses because they help increase sales. However, some advertisements can be misleading or too repetitive, which may annoy people and encourage unnecessary spending.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Why are many advertisements endorsed by celebrities? How useful are they?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> I think companies use celebrities because famous people can attract attention very quickly. Fans often trust or admire celebrities, so they may be more willing to buy the products being promoted. Honestly, I think this strategy is quite effective, especially among young consumers.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What is the most important factor in an advertisement?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> In my opinion, the most important factor is creativity. If an advertisement is interesting, memorable, or emotional, people are more likely to pay attention to it. At the same time, the message also needs to be clear and easy to understand.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. Why are some advertisements boring?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"> Well, some ads are boring because they’re too repetitive or lack creativity. Sometimes companies focus too much on selling the product and forget to make the content entertaining or relatable. As a result, people may just skip the advertisement completely.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>5. Is advertising important for a company? Why?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yes, definitely. Advertising is extremely important because it helps companies promote their products and build brand awareness. Without advertising, many businesses would struggle to attract customers, especially in highly competitive markets.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>9 Describe a live sports event you watched and liked</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">What it was</p>
<p dir="ltr">When and where you watched it</p>
<p dir="ltr">Who you watched it with </p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why you liked it </p>
<p dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about a live football match that I watched and really enjoyed. It was the final match of a regional football tournament involving the Vietnamese national team.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I watched it about a year ago at a café near my house with a group of close friends. The café was completely packed with football fans, so the atmosphere was incredibly exciting and energetic. Everyone was cheering, shouting, and reacting to every moment of the game.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The match itself was really intense because both teams played very well, and the score was close throughout the game. What made it even more exciting was that Vietnam scored the winning goal near the end of the match, so the whole crowd suddenly became super emotional and excited.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Honestly, the reason why I liked it so much was not only because the game was entertaining but also because of the atmosphere and the people around me. Watching sports live with other fans feels completely different from watching alone at home. I mean, everyone was celebrating together, and it created a really strong sense of connection.</p>
<p dir="ltr">So yeah, it’s definitely one of the most memorable sports events I’ve ever watched, and I’d love to experience something like that again in the future.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Why do some people like to watch sports events?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I think people enjoy watching sports events because they’re exciting and entertaining. Sports can also create a strong sense of competition and emotion, especially when people support their favorite teams or athletes. Besides that, watching sports is often a social activity that helps people relax and connect with others.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. Where do people normally watch sports events?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Nowadays, most people watch sports events at home on TV or online using their phones and laptops. Some people also go to cafés or sports bars to enjoy the atmosphere with other fans. Of course, many sports lovers prefer watching matches live in stadiums because the experience feels more exciting.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. What are the advantages of watching sports events online?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Watching sports online is very convenient because people can watch matches anytime and anywhere. It’s also cheaper than buying tickets to a stadium. Another advantage is that viewers can replay important moments or check match highlights easily.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. What sports matches are suitable for children to attend?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think family-friendly sports like football, basketball, swimming, or badminton are suitable for children. These events are usually entertaining and can encourage kids to become more interested in sports and healthy activities. However, I think the environment should be safe and not too aggressive or crowded.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>10 Describe a time when you worked in a group</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">You should say:</p>
<p dir="ltr">What you did</p>
<p dir="ltr">Who you worked with</p>
<p dir="ltr">What problems you faced</p>
<p dir="ltr">And explain why you worked in the group </p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Sample</strong>:</p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I’d like to talk about a time when I worked on a group presentation at university. It was for one of my marketing classes, and our group had to prepare a presentation about consumer behavior.</p>
<p dir="ltr">I worked with four of my classmates. We divided the tasks among ourselves, so some people focused on research while others designed the slides or prepared the speaking parts. I was mainly responsible for organizing the ideas and presenting part of the project.</p>
<p dir="ltr">To be honest, we did face a few problems. The biggest one was probably scheduling because everyone had different timetables, so it was hard to arrange meetings. Also, there were times when some members didn’t respond quickly, which slowed the progress down a bit.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Even so, we decided to work as a group because the project was quite large and required different skills. I mean, if one person had done everything alone, it would’ve been really stressful and time-consuming.</p>
<p dir="ltr">In the end, I actually enjoyed the experience because I learned how to communicate better and cooperate with different people. Plus, our presentation went pretty well, so I felt really satisfied afterward.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>1. Why do some people prefer to work by themselves?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Well, I think some people prefer working alone because they can focus better and manage their own time more freely. You know, when working in a group, there can sometimes be disagreements or communication problems, which may slow things down. So for independent people, working alone often feels more efficient and less stressful.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>2. What should a leader do to make team members want to follow him or her?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">I think a good leader should be supportive, responsible, and a good listener. Instead of just giving orders, they should communicate clearly and respect everyone’s opinions. Also, if a leader sets a good example and works hard, team members are more likely to trust and follow them willingly.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>3. Should students learn to do group work?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Yeah, definitely. I think group work is really important because it helps students develop communication and teamwork skills. In real life and future jobs, people usually have to cooperate with others, so learning how to work in a team from a young age can be very useful.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>4. What group tasks are there in schools?</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Hmm, there are quite a lot actually, such as group presentations, science projects, discussions, and sports activities. Sometimes students also work together on research assignments or creative projects. These activities encourage them to share ideas and learn from one another.</p>', NULL, 'speaking', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'https://cms.ieltspredictiontest.com/media/images/6-1779681586.png', 'published', true, 0, '[]', '{}', '2026-05-25 04:02:24.991+00', '2026-05-25 03:33:02.78775+00');
INSERT INTO public.sample_essays VALUES ('76c134df-f076-4f74-a8f4-bf1ffa1f3dc1', '[FORECAST SPEAKING] FREE Dự Đoán IELTS SPEAKING TUẦN (11/5-18/5)', 'forecast-speaking-free-du-doan-ielts-speaking-tuan-115-185', '<h1 dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">FORECAST SPEAKING 11/5 -18/5</h1>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Lưu ý: đây chỉ là những đề có xu hướng được hỏi nhiều trong phòng thi, sau khi ôn những đề này vẫn cần ôn các đề còn lại trong forecast</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Sử dụng <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-NfjggXjSs-ielts-prediction-ai">Chat Bot</a> để luyện tập tại nhà </p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">Tham gia nhóm dự đoán : <span style="color: #3598db;"><a style="color: #3598db;" href="https://zalo.me/g/rccckf822">https://zalo.me/g/rccckf822</a></span></p>
<div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" align="left">
<table style="margin-left: 40px; border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 90.6433%;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 31.6507%;" width="248"><col style="width: 68.3493%;" width="379"></colgroup>
<tbody style="padding-left: 40px;">
<tr style="padding-left: 40px;">
<td style="padding: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong>Part One</strong></p>
<p style="line-height: 2; padding-left: 40px;">Where you live</p>
<p style="line-height: 2; padding-left: 40px;">Work/study</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">1 Park and garden</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">2 Headphones</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">3 Outer space</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">4 Shopping</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">5 Singing </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">6  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">7  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">8  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">9  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">10  </p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong>Part Two/Three</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">1 Describe a time when you encouraged someone to do something that he/she didn''t want to do</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">2 Describe a boring place</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">3 Describe a child who loves drawing/painting</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">4 Describe a friend from your childhood </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">5 Describe a tall building you like or dislike</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">6  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">7  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">8  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">9  </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">10  </p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr></div>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Examiner to ask questions from EITHER Frame 1 or Frame 2</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 1 (Where you live now)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about where you live now</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which town or city do you live in now?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are there any things you don’t like about your area? (What are they?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you think you will continue to live there for a long time? (Why? Why not?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What are some changes in the area recently?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you live in a house or an apartment?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What is your favourite room in your home? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What things make your home pleasant to live in? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are the people in your neighbourhood nice and friendly?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you know any of your neighbours?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Is the place where you live quiet or noisy?</p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 2 (Work/ Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about what you do. Do you work or are you a student?</p>
<p dir="ltr">(Work)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What kind of work do you do?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you – the people you work with or the work you do? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you work best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Would you like to change the place you work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">(Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your studies? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you—the teachers or the other students on your course? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How much time do you spend studying every week?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How do you usually travel to the city where you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you study best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Have you always wanted to study this subject/ these subjects (Why/ Why not?)</p>
<hr>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>1 Park and gardens</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">1. Did you like going to parks as a child?</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you still like going to parks now?</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Would you like to see more parks in your city?</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Are there any parks you want to go to in the future?<br><br></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>2 Headphones</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you use headphones?</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. In what conditions would you not use headphones?</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. When would you use headphones?</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. What type of headphones do you use?<br><br></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>3 Outer space and stars</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">1. Have you ever learnt about outer space and stars?</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you like science fiction movies? Why?</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Do you want to know more about outer space?</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you want to go into outer space in the future?<br><br></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8;"><strong>4 Shopping</strong></span></p>
<p dir="ltr">1. How often do you go shopping?</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you prefer online shopping or in-store shopping?</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Have you ever returned anything you bought online?</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you like shopping?<br><br></p>
<p dir="ltr"><strong><span style="background-color: #fbeeb8;">5 Singing </span></strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you like singing? Why?</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Have you ever learnt how to sing?</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Who do you want to sing for?</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you think singing can bring happiness to people?<br><br></p>', NULL, 'speaking', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'https://cms.ieltspredictiontest.com/media/images/forecast-writing-tu---n-11-5-18-55-1778496794.png', 'published', false, 0, '[]', '{}', '2026-05-12 03:50:50.042+00', '2026-05-11 10:54:33.291529+00');
INSERT INTO public.sample_essays VALUES ('1ff797df-89dd-4baf-b09f-d6d35cba62d3', '[FORECAST SPEAKING] Dự Đoán IELTS SPEAKING TUẦN (11/5-18/5)', 'forecast-speaking-du-doan-ielts-speaking-tuan-115-115', '<h1 dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">FORECAST SPEAKING 11/5 -18/5</h1>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Lưu ý: đây chỉ là những đề có xu hướng được hỏi nhiều trong phòng thi, sau khi ôn những đề này vẫn cần ôn các đề còn lại trong forecast</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;">Sử dụng <a href="https://chatgpt.com/g/g-NfjggXjSs-ielts-prediction-ai">Chat Bot</a> để luyện tập tại nhà </p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>PDF </strong>tải<strong> </strong><span style="color: #236fa1;"><a style="color: #236fa1;" href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1GQV72i5DcmB4HCGTzs-TMghdifvm-Jku/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tại đây</a></span></span></p>
<div dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" align="left">
<table style="margin-left: 40px; border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-spacing: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 90.6433%;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 31.6507%;" width="248"><col style="width: 68.3493%;" width="379"></colgroup>
<tbody style="padding-left: 40px;">
<tr style="padding-left: 40px;">
<td style="padding: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong>Part One</strong></p>
<p style="line-height: 2; padding-left: 40px;">Where you live</p>
<p style="line-height: 2; padding-left: 40px;">Work/study</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">1 Park and garden</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">2 Headphones</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">3 Outer space</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">4 Shopping</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">5 Singing </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">6 Social media</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">7 Gifts</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">8 Morning</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">9 Clothing</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">10 Watches</p>
</td>
<td style="padding: 1px; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;">
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong>Part Two/Three</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">1 Describe a time when you encouraged someone to do something that he/she didn''t want to do</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">2 Describe a boring place</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">3 Describe a child who loves drawing/painting</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">4 Describe a friend from your childhood </p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">5 Describe a tall building you like or dislike</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">6 Describe a person who loves to grow plants (e.g. vegetables, flowers) at home or in the garden</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">7 Describe a boring place</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">8 Describe a home that you like to visit but do not want to live in</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">9 Describe a person who has chosen a career in the medical field (e.g a doctor, a nurse)</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;" role="presentation">10 Describe an item on which you spent more than expected </p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr></div>
<p dir="ltr"><strong>Examiner to ask questions from EITHER Frame 1 or Frame 2</strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 1 (Where you live now)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about where you live now</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which town or city do you live in now?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are there any things you don’t like about your area? (What are they?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you think you will continue to live there for a long time? (Why? Why not?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What are some changes in the area recently?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you live in a house or an apartment?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What is your favourite room in your home? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What things make your home pleasant to live in? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Are the people in your neighbourhood nice and friendly?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you know any of your neighbours?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Is the place where you live quiet or noisy?</p>
<p dir="ltr">Frame 2 (Work/ Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">Let’s talk about what you do. Do you work or are you a student?</p>
<p dir="ltr">(Work)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What kind of work do you do?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you – the people you work with or the work you do? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you work best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Would you like to change the place you work? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr" style="padding-left: 40px;"><strong> </strong></p>
<p dir="ltr">(Study)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- What do you find most interesting about your studies? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Which is more important to you—the teachers or the other students on your course? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How much time do you spend studying every week?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- How do you usually travel to the city where you study?</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Do you study best in the morning or the afternoon? (Why?)</p>
<p dir="ltr">- Have you always wanted to study this subject/ these subjects (Why/ Why not?)</p>
<hr>
<h2 dir="ltr">1 Park and gardens</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Did you like going to parks as a child?<br>Yeah, definitely. I used to go to parks quite a lot when I was a kid, especially on weekends with my family. I mean, parks were probably one of the few places where I could run around freely, play games, and hang out with my friends. Looking back, those trips were actually a big part of my childhood.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you still like going to parks now?<br>Yeah, I do, although I go there for different reasons now. These days, I usually visit parks when I need a break from studying or work because they’re much quieter and less stressful than crowded places. Sometimes I just take a walk, listen to music, or simply sit there to clear my mind.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Would you like to see more parks in your city?<br>Absolutely. I think more parks would really improve people’s quality of life, especially in big cities where there’s a lot of traffic and pollution. Parks provide green spaces where people can exercise, relax, or spend time with their families. Plus, they make the city look much more livable and attractive.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Are there any parks you want to go to in the future?<br>Hmm, yeah, definitely. I’d love to visit some famous national parks abroad, especially places with amazing scenery and wildlife. For example, I’ve always wanted to see places like Yellowstone or Banff because, you know, they look incredibly peaceful and breathtaking in photos and videos.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">2 Headphones</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you use headphones?<br>Yeah, I do, pretty much every day. I usually use them when I’m listening to music, watching videos, or studying in noisy places. I mean, headphones help me focus better and avoid distractions.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. In what conditions would you not use headphones?<br>Hmm, probably when I’m walking on busy streets or crossing the road because it can be dangerous if I can’t hear what’s happening around me. I also avoid using them when talking to other people since it might seem a bit rude.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. When would you use headphones?<br>I mostly use them when I’m studying, working out, or travelling on public transport. Sometimes I also put them on when I just want to relax and enjoy some music without disturbing other people.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. What type of headphones do you use?<br>I currently use wireless earbuds because they’re really convenient and easy to carry around. Plus, I don’t have to deal with tangled wires, which is honestly one of the things I hated about traditional headphones.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">3 Outer space and stars</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Have you ever learnt about outer space and stars?<br>Yes, I have. I remember learning some basic things about the solar system and constellations in primary school. I was always fascinated by the universe, even though I didn’t go too deep into the science behind it.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you like science fiction movies? Why?<br>Absolutely! I really enjoy sci-fi movies because they often explore the unknown, like time travel, aliens, or life on other planets. They spark my imagination and make me think about what might be possible in the future.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Do you want to know more about outer space?<br>Yes, I do. I think space is full of mystery, and there’s still so much we don’t understand. I’d love to learn more about things like black holes, Mars exploration, or how astronauts live in space.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you want to go into outer space in the future?<br>To be honest, I think it would be an amazing experience, but I’m not sure I’m brave enough! The idea of floating in zero gravity sounds fun, but space travel also seems risky and uncomfortable. So maybe I’d just enjoy it through documentaries</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">4 Shopping</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. How often do you go shopping?<br>Hmm, I’d say I go shopping quite regularly, probably once or twice a week. Most of the time, I just buy daily necessities like food or skincare products. But occasionally, I also shop for clothes or other things when I need them.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you prefer online shopping or in-store shopping?<br>I probably prefer online shopping because it’s much more convenient and saves a lot of time. I mean, I can easily compare prices and order things without leaving my house. That said, for clothes or shoes, I still prefer shopping in-store so I can try them on first.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Have you ever returned anything you bought online?<br>Yeah, I have, actually. Once I ordered a shirt online, but when it arrived, the size was completely different from what I expected. So I ended up returning it and getting a refund. Luckily, the process was pretty straightforward.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you like shopping?<br>Yeah, I do, to some extent. I think shopping can be enjoyable, especially when I’m buying something I really like. But honestly, I’m not the type of person who spends hours shopping because it can get tiring after a while.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">5 Singing </h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you like singing? Why?<br>Yeah, I actually do, even though I’m not a great singer or anything. I mostly sing when I’m alone or hanging out with close friends because it helps me unwind and forget about stress for a while. Also, I think music has a way of improving my mood almost instantly.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Have you ever learnt how to sing?<br>Hmm, not professionally, no. I’ve never taken singing lessons, but I sometimes learn by listening to songs and singing along. I mean, it’s more of a hobby for me rather than something I seriously want to pursue.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Who do you want to sing for?<br>I’d probably sing for my friends or family since I feel comfortable around them. Honestly, performing in front of strangers would make me quite nervous. But yeah, singing with people I’m close to is usually fun and relaxing.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you think singing can bring happiness to people?<br>Yeah, definitely. I think singing is a great way for people to express their emotions and connect with others. For example, upbeat songs can create a really positive atmosphere, while emotional songs can help people feel understood or comforted.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">6 Social media</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1 Have you ever posted anything on social media?<br>Yeah, I have, but not that often, to be honest. I usually post photos when I hang out with friends or travel somewhere interesting. Apart from that, I don’t really share much because, you know, I prefer to keep my personal life private.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2 When did you start using social media?<br>Hmm, let me think… I’d say I started using it when I was around 13 or 14. That was when most of my classmates were already on it, so I kind of just followed and used it to stay in touch.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3 Do you think you spend too much time on social media?<br>Yeah, sometimes I do, to be honest. I mean, I can get distracted quite easily just scrolling through videos. Before I know it, I’ve spent way more time than I planned, so I’m trying to cut down a bit.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4 Do your friends use social media?<br>Yeah, pretty much all of them do. I mean, it’s basically the main way we communicate these days, whether it’s chatting, sharing updates, or, you know, making plans together.</p>
<p dir="ltr">5 What do people often do on social media?<br>Well, I’d say most people just scroll through their feeds or watch videos. But, you know, some people also use it for studying or even running small businesses, so it’s not just for entertainment.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">7 Gifts </h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. What gift have you received recently?<br>Well, just a few weeks ago, one of my close friends gave me a book for my birthday — it was a novel I’d been wanting to read for a while. It wasn’t anything flashy, but it felt really thoughtful because she remembered what I liked. I was honestly touched by how personal it was.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Have you ever sent handmade gifts to others?<br>Yes, actually. Back in high school, I made a scrapbook for my best friend’s birthday. It had photos, handwritten notes, and little drawings. It took quite a bit of time, but I really enjoyed the process. I think handmade gifts are special because they show genuine effort and creativity.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Have you ever received a great gift?<br>Definitely. One of the most memorable gifts I got was a laptop from my parents when I got into university. It was both useful and meaningful because it marked a big milestone in my life. I still use it every day, and it reminds me of how supportive they are.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. What do you consider when choosing a gift?<br>I usually think about the person’s personality and interests. For example, if someone enjoys cooking, I might get them a unique kitchen gadget. I also try to consider the occasion — like whether it’s a birthday, graduation, or just a small thank-you gift — because that can influence the style or price.</p>
<p dir="ltr">5. Do you think you are good at choosing gifts?<br>I’d say I’m pretty decent. I always try to be thoughtful and avoid generic things. I enjoy the process of finding something that will make the other person smile. Of course, it doesn’t always work out perfectly, but I think the effort really counts.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">8 Morning time</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you like getting up early in the morning?<br>To be honest, not really. I’m more of a night owl, so waking up early is a bit of a struggle for me. But when I do manage to get up early, I actually enjoy the peaceful atmosphere — everything feels calm and quiet, which is quite refreshing.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. What do you usually do in the morning?<br>Well, on weekdays, I usually start my day by washing my face, brushing my teeth, and making a cup of tea or coffee. Then I check my to-do list and begin studying or working, depending on the day. I try to avoid checking social media right away, just to stay focused.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. What did you do in the morning when you were little? Why?<br>When I was a kid, my morning routine was pretty simple. I’d wake up, get dressed in my school uniform, and have breakfast — usually bánh mì or a bowl of phở. My mom always made sure I had a full stomach before heading to school. Back then, everything was very routine and guided by my parents.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Are there any differences between what you do in the morning now and what you did in the past?<br>Yes, definitely. In the past, my mornings were quite passive — I just followed whatever my parents told me to do. But now, I have more control over my schedule. I plan my mornings around productivity, like doing revision or checking emails. It’s more structured, but also more flexible in a way.</p>
<p dir="ltr">5. Do you spend your mornings doing the same things on both weekends and weekdays? Why?<br>Not really. On weekdays, my mornings are quite rushed because I have classes or work to get to. But on weekends, I allow myself to sleep in a bit and take things slow. I might cook something nice for breakfast or go out for a coffee with friends. It’s my way of recharging after a hectic week.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">9 Clothing</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. What kind of clothes do you like to wear?<br>Well, I usually prefer simple and casual clothes, like T-shirts, jeans, or hoodies. I mean, comfort is probably the most important thing for me. But sometimes, if I’m going to a special event, I’ll dress a bit more formally.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Do you prefer to wear comfortable and casual clothes or smart clothes?<br>I’d definitely choose comfortable and casual clothes most of the time. They’re more practical for daily activities, and I feel more relaxed wearing them. That said, I still think smart clothes are important for formal occasions or professional settings.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Do you like wearing T-shirts?<br>Yeah, absolutely. T-shirts are probably the clothing item I wear the most because they’re comfortable and easy to match with other clothes. Plus, they work well in hot weather, which is great where I live.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you spend a lot of time choosing clothes?<br>Hmm, not really. I usually keep things simple, so I don’t spend too much time deciding what to wear. Unless it’s for an important occasion, I just pick something comfortable and suitable for the weather.</p>
<h2 dir="ltr">10 Watch</h2>
<p dir="ltr">1. Do you wear a watch?<br>Yeah, I do, but not all the time. I usually wear a watch when I go to school or go out because it’s more convenient than checking my phone all the time. Plus, I think watches can also be a nice fashion accessory.</p>
<p dir="ltr">2. Have you ever got a watch as a gift?<br>Yeah, I have. I remember getting a watch from my parents on my birthday a few years ago. It wasn’t too expensive, but, you know, it meant a lot to me because it was a special gift from them.</p>
<p dir="ltr">3. Why do some people wear expensive watches?<br>Well, I think there are a few reasons. Some people wear expensive watches to show their social status or wealth, while others simply appreciate the design and craftsmanship. I mean, luxury watches are sometimes seen as a fashion statement as well.</p>
<p dir="ltr">4. Do you think it is important to wear a watch? Why?<br>Hmm, I’d say it depends on the person. For me, wearing a watch is quite useful because it helps me manage my time more easily. Also, even though phones can tell the time, watches are still more convenient in some situations.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;">1 Describe a time when you encouraged someone to do something that he/she didn''t want to do</span></strong></span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who he or she is</p>
<p>What you encouraged him/her to do</p>
<p>How he/she reacted</p>
<p>And explain why you encouraged him/her to do it</p>
<p><strong>SAMPLE </strong></p>
<p>Well, the person I encouraged was my close friend, Linh. We’ve known each other for years, and she’s always been quite smart, but, you know, she lacked confidence in English. About a year ago, I suggested that she start preparing for the IELTS exam because it would open up more opportunities for her, like studying abroad or getting a better job.</p>
<p>At first, she really didn’t want to do it. She kept saying things like, “My English is terrible,” or “I don’t have time for such a difficult test.” She looked nervous every time someone mentioned IELTS, and honestly, I could understand her fear because the test sounds intimidating.</p>
<p>I encouraged her by showing her that the process didn’t have to be overwhelming. I told her that we could study together, set small goals, and practise step by step. I also shared my own experience and explained how much IELTS helped me improve my speaking and writing skills. Little by little, she started to see the benefits.</p>
<p>At first, she reacted quite hesitantly, but after a few conversations — and maybe after I kept pushing her gently — she agreed to give it a try. She started with simple speaking topics, then writing structures, and eventually built her confidence.</p>
<p>In the end, I encouraged her because I genuinely believed she had the potential to do well if she just took the first step. And actually, a few months later, she managed to get a pretty solid score, which made both of us incredibly proud.</p>
<p><br><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. How can leaders encourage their employees?</strong></p>
<p>Well, I think leaders can encourage their employees mainly by recognising their efforts and offering constructive feedback. You know, when people feel appreciated, they naturally become more motivated. Another effective way is giving them opportunities—like training, promotions, or chances to take on new responsibilities. And of course, creating a supportive environment where employees feel comfortable sharing ideas also plays a huge role.</p>
<p><strong>2. When should parents encourage their children?</strong></p>
<p>I’d say parents should encourage their children whenever they’re trying something new or facing challenges. Kids, you know, often doubt themselves, so support helps build their confidence. Another important moment is when children make mistakes. Instead of criticising them, parents should motivate them to learn from the experience and try again. Encouragement at the right time can really shape a child’s mindset</p>
<p><strong>3. What kind of encouragement should parents give?</strong></p>
<p>Well, I think the most valuable encouragement is emotional support—things like praising effort, showing trust, and being patient. Parents should avoid pushing their children too much. Instead of saying “You must succeed,” they should say things like “I believe in you” or “Just do your best.” Practical support is also important, such as helping kids practise a skill or providing resources for learning.</p>
<p><strong>4. Do you think some people are better than others at persuading?</strong></p>
<p>Oh yes, definitely. Some people have better communication skills and are naturally more confident, so they can persuade others more easily. Others are good at reading people’s emotions and adjusting their approach, which is also part of persuasion. But I believe persuasion is a skill that can be learned. With practice—like improving speaking skills, understanding psychology, and showing empathy—most people can become good at it.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;">2 Describe a boring place</span></strong></span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Where it is</p>
<p>Who you went there with</p>
<p>What you did there</p>
<p>And explain why you think it is a boring place </p>
<p><br><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about a place that I found quite boring, which was a history museum that I visited a few years ago.</p>
<p>It’s located in my city, and I went there with a few classmates as part of a school trip. At first, I thought it would be interesting because I don’t usually go to museums, so I expected to learn something new.</p>
<p>While we were there, we mainly walked around looking at old photos, historical objects, and information boards. Our teacher also asked us to take notes for a small assignment, so, you know, we had to spend quite a long time reading everything.</p>
<p>Honestly, I found the place pretty boring because the atmosphere was too quiet and there wasn’t much interaction. I mean, most of the exhibits were just displayed behind glass with long descriptions, which made it hard to stay focused. Also, history isn’t really my favourite subject, so after a while I started to lose interest.</p>
<p>That said, I still think museums are useful for learning about culture and history. It’s just that this particular place wasn’t really my type.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Why do most children think education is boring?</strong><br> Well, I think one reason is that some subjects are taught in a very theoretical and repetitive way. I mean, if students only memorize information without doing practical activities, they can lose interest quite quickly. Also, a lot of children nowadays are more attracted to entertainment like games or social media, so studying may seem less exciting to them.</p>
<p><strong>2. Why aren’t young people willing to listen to the experiences of older people?</strong><br> Hmm, I think it’s partly because younger people nowadays want to make their own decisions and learn from their own experiences. Sometimes they feel that older generations may not fully understand modern lifestyles or current trends. But honestly, I still think advice from older people can be really valuable.</p>
<p><strong>3. What can people do when they feel bored?</strong><br> There are actually lots of things people can do. For example, they can listen to music, watch movies, play sports, or hang out with friends. Some people also try learning new skills or hobbies because it helps them stay productive and mentally refreshed.</p>
<p><strong>4. Why are some teachers’ classes boring? Are there any solutions?</strong><br> I think classes can become boring when teachers focus too much on lectures and don’t interact with students. If lessons are too long or repetitive, students may stop paying attention. As for solutions, I think teachers could include more discussions, games, or practical activities to make lessons more engaging and interactive.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;"><strong>3 Describe a child who loves drawing/painting</strong></span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who he/she is</p>
<p>How/when you knew him/her</p>
<p>How often he/she draws/paints</p>
<p>And explain why you think he/she loves drawing/painting</p>
<p><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, the child I’d like to talk about is my little cousin, Minh. He’s around eight years old, and actually, I’ve known him since he was born because our families are really close. He’s always been a bit different from other kids — you know, calmer, more focused, and kind of more imaginative.</p>
<p>He draws or paints almost every single day. Whenever I visit his house, he’s either sketching animals, colouring cartoon characters, or creating these little comic strips based on his daily life. His parents even bought him a big art table and a huge set of crayons because he kept running out of materials. And honestly, once he starts drawing, he can sit there for hours without getting distracted, which is pretty impressive for a child his age.</p>
<p>I think he loves drawing for a couple of reasons. First, he’s a little shy, so drawing is his way of expressing himself. Instead of talking a lot, he uses pictures to show what he’s thinking or feeling. Second, he has a really strong imagination. He notices small details that most adults ignore, and he enjoys turning those details into colourful drawings. And lastly, drawing genuinely makes him happy — you can see it in the way his eyes light up whenever he finishes a picture.</p>
<p>So yeah, I truly believe he has a natural talent for art, and if he keeps practising, he might become a really talented artist in the future.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is the right age for a child to learn drawing?</strong></p>
<p>Well, I don’t think there’s a strict “right” age, but most children can start drawing as early as two or three years old. At that age, they enjoy scribbling and experimenting with colours. As they grow older, around five or six, they can begin learning basic techniques. What matters most is that children learn in a relaxed and enjoyable environment, instead of being pressured to be perfect.</p>
<p><strong>2. Why do most children draw more often than adults do?</strong></p>
<p>I think it’s because children naturally express themselves through drawing. They have active imaginations and don’t worry about whether their artwork looks good or not. Adults, on the other hand, tend to be more self-conscious and busy with work or responsibilities, so they lose that creative habit over time. Plus, children treat drawing as playtime, while adults often see it as a skill that requires talent.</p>
<p><strong>3. Why do some people visit galleries or museums instead of viewing artworks online?</strong></p>
<p>Well, visiting a gallery or museum gives people a much deeper experience. You can see the real textures, colours, and scale of the artwork, which you simply can’t feel through a screen. The atmosphere of a museum also helps people focus and appreciate the art more. And for many, it’s a social or cultural activity — they enjoy the space, the storytelling, and even the conversations with others.</p>
<p><strong>4. Do you think galleries and museums should be free of charge?</strong></p>
<p>To some extent, yes. Making museums free encourages more people, especially students and low-income families, to learn about culture and history. However, museums also need funding for maintenance, exhibitions, and staff. So a good balance might be free entry on certain days, or discounted tickets for young people. That way, culture stays accessible without financial pressure on the institution.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: #f8cac6; font-size: 14pt;"><strong>4 Describe a friend from your childhood </strong></span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who he/she is</p>
<p>Where and how you met each other</p>
<p>What you often did together</p>
<p>And explain what made you like him/her </p>
<p><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about one of my childhood friends named Minh. We’ve known each other for a really long time, probably since primary school.</p>
<p>We first met when we were in the same class in grade 3. At that time, we sat next to each other, and, you know, we became friends quite naturally because we had similar interests. We both enjoyed playing video games and watching cartoons.</p>
<p>When we were younger, we spent a lot of time together after school. Sometimes we played football in the neighborhood, and other times we just hung out at each other’s houses. During weekends, we also used to ride our bikes around the area or go to small convenience stores to buy snacks.</p>
<p>What I liked most about him was that he was really friendly and supportive. I mean, he was the kind of person who was always willing to help others. We also got along very well because we had a similar sense of humor, so we always had a lot of fun together.</p>
<p>Even though we’re both busier now, we still keep in touch from time to time, and I’m really glad that our friendship has lasted for so many years.</p>
<p><br> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Do you still keep in touch with your friends from childhood? Why or why not?</strong></p>
<p>Yeah, I still keep in touch with a few of them. Even though we’re all busier now, we still text each other or meet up once in a while. I think it’s because we’ve known each other for such a long time, so the friendship feels really genuine.</p>
<p><strong>2. How important is childhood friendship to children?</strong></p>
<p>I think it’s very important because childhood friendships can help children develop social skills and learn how to communicate with others. Also, having close friends at a young age can make children feel more confident and emotionally supported.</p>
<p><strong>3. What do you think of communicating via social media?</strong></p>
<p>Well, I think it’s really convenient, especially for people who live far away from each other. I mean, social media makes it much easier to stay connected and communicate instantly. But at the same time, I don’t think online conversations are always as meaningful as face-to-face ones.</p>
<p><strong>4. Do you think online communication through social media will replace face-to-face communication?</strong></p>
<p>Hmm, probably not completely. I think social media is useful for staying in touch, but face-to-face communication is still more personal and natural. You know, when people meet in person, it’s easier to understand emotions and build stronger relationships.</p>
<p><strong>5. What''s the difference between having younger friends and older friends?</strong></p>
<p>Well, younger friends are usually more energetic and fun to hang out with, while older friends tend to be more experienced and mature. I think both are valuable in different ways because you can learn different things from them.</p>
<p><strong>6. Has technology changed people''s friendships? How?</strong></p>
<p>Yeah, definitely. Technology has made it much easier for people to stay connected through messaging apps and social media. But at the same time, I think some friendships have become a bit less personal because people now communicate online more often than in real life.</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;">5 Describe a tall building you like or dislike</span></strong></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>What it is used for </p>
<p>Where it is</p>
<p>What it looks like</p>
<p>And explain why you like/dislike it</p>
<p><br><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about a tall building that I really like, which is Landmark 81 in Ho Chi Minh City. It’s currently one of the tallest buildings in Vietnam and is quite famous among both locals and tourists.</p>
<p>The building is mainly used as a mixed-use complex, so it includes apartments, offices, shopping centers, restaurants, and even a hotel. I mean, it’s basically like a small modern city inside one building.</p>
<p>In terms of appearance, the building looks really modern and impressive. It’s covered in glass, so it reflects sunlight beautifully during the day, and at night it lights up, which makes the city skyline look much more attractive. Whenever I see it from a distance, it really stands out.</p>
<p>The reason why I like this building is not only because of its design but also because it represents how modern and developed the city has become. Plus, the view from the top is absolutely amazing. I went there once with my friends, and honestly, seeing the whole city from above was such a memorable experience.</p>
<p>So yeah, I think it’s one of the most impressive buildings in my country.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Are there many tall buildings in your country?</strong></p>
<p>Yeah, definitely. In recent years, a lot of tall buildings have been built, especially in big cities like Ho Chi Minh City or Hanoi. I mean, as the economy develops, there’s a growing demand for offices, apartments, and shopping centers, so skyscrapers are becoming much more common.</p>
<p><strong>2. What are the differences between those tall buildings in your country?</strong></p>
<p>Well, they differ in several ways, like design, purpose, and location. Some buildings are mainly used for offices or businesses, while others are residential apartments or hotels. Also, newer buildings usually look more modern and include advanced technology, whereas older ones tend to have simpler designs.</p>
<p><strong>3. Why are different places laid out and designed differently?</strong><br> I think it depends on factors like culture, climate, and the purpose of the place. For example, crowded urban areas are often designed to save space and support transportation, while countryside areas usually focus more on open spaces and nature. Cultural preferences and local lifestyles can also influence how places are designed.</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="background-color: #f8cac6; font-size: 14pt;">6 Describe a person who loves to grow plants (e.g. vegetables, flowers) at home or in the garden</span></strong></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who this person is</p>
<p>What plants he/she grows</p>
<p>How he/she grows the plants </p>
<p>And explain why he/she loves growing plants</p>
<p><br><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about my grandmother, who absolutely loves growing plants at home. She spends a lot of time taking care of her small garden, which is located right in front of her house.</p>
<p>She grows a variety of plants, especially flowers and vegetables. For example, she has roses, orchids, and some small vegetable plants like tomatoes and herbs. I mean, her garden is always full of greenery, so it looks really peaceful and relaxing.</p>
<p>As for how she grows them, she waters the plants every morning and carefully checks if they’re healthy. She also uses natural fertilizer and sometimes moves the pots around to make sure the plants get enough sunlight. Honestly, I’m quite impressed by how patient and dedicated she is.</p>
<p>The reason why she enjoys growing plants so much is that it helps her relax and stay active. She once told me that gardening makes her feel calmer and happier, especially after a stressful day. Plus, I think she simply enjoys seeing things grow and bloom over time.</p>
<p>So yeah, whenever I visit her house, I always feel really comfortable because of the fresh and peaceful atmosphere created by all those plants.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What are the advantages of growing vegetables or flowers at home?</strong></p>
<p>Well, I think there are quite a few benefits. For one thing, growing vegetables at home can provide fresher and healthier food. As for flowers or plants, they can make the house look more beautiful and relaxing. Plus, gardening is also a good way to reduce stress and spend free time productively.</p>
<p><strong>2. Do many people grow vegetables or flowers at home in your country?</strong></p>
<p>Yeah, quite a lot of people do, especially older people or families living in suburban and rural areas. Some grow vegetables in their gardens, while others plant flowers or small plants on balconies or rooftops to decorate their homes.</p>
<p><strong>3. Is it easy to grow plants at home?</strong><br> Hmm, I think it depends on the type of plant and how much experience a person has. Some plants are pretty easy to take care of, but others require more time and attention. People also need enough sunlight, water, and space for the plants to grow properly.</p>
<p><strong>4. Why do some people like to grow plants?</strong></p>
<p>I think many people enjoy it because gardening can be really relaxing and satisfying. I mean, watching plants grow over time gives people a sense of achievement. Also, some people simply love nature and want to create a greener living space.</p>
<p><strong>5. Why do some people prefer to grow their own fruits and vegetables instead of buying them from the market?</strong></p>
<p>Well, one reason is that they want healthier and safer food because they can control how the plants are grown. Also, home-grown fruits and vegetables are usually fresher. For some people, it’s also a way to save money and enjoy gardening at the same time.</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="background-color: #f8cac6; font-size: 14pt;">7 Describe a boring place</span></strong></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Where it is</p>
<p>Who you went there with</p>
<p>What you did there</p>
<p>And explain why you think it is a boring place </p>
<p><br><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about a place that I found really boring, which was a small exhibition hall that I visited during a school trip a few years ago.</p>
<p>It was located in my city, and I went there with my classmates and teachers. Honestly, at first, I thought it would be quite interesting because I don’t usually visit places like that. But after spending some time there, I started to lose interest.</p>
<p>While we were there, we mainly walked around looking at old pictures, documents, and historical objects. Our teacher also asked us to read the information boards and take notes for a class assignment, so, you know, it felt more like studying than actually enjoying the trip.</p>
<p>The main reason why I thought it was boring was that there wasn’t much interaction or entertainment. Everything was very quiet and repetitive, and most of the displays just had long written descriptions. Also, we stayed there for quite a long time, so I got tired and couldn’t really focus anymore.</p>
<p>That said, I still think places like that can be educational and useful for learning about history or culture. It’s just that, personally, I prefer places with more activities and a livelier atmosphere.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Why do most children think education is boring?</strong></p>
<p> Well, I think one major reason is that some schools focus too much on memorization and exams rather than practical learning. I mean, if students just sit in class listening to long lectures all day, they can easily lose interest. Also, compared to things like games or social media, studying may seem less entertaining to children.</p>
<p><strong>2. Why aren’t young people willing to listen to the experiences of older people?</strong></p>
<p>Hmm, I think young people nowadays prefer figuring things out by themselves instead of simply following advice from older generations. Sometimes they also feel that older people may not fully understand modern lifestyles or current problems. But honestly, I still think older people’s experiences can be really helpful in many situations.</p>
<p><strong>3. What can people do when they feel bored?</strong></p>
<p>There are actually lots of ways to deal with boredom. For example, people can watch movies, listen to music, play sports, or spend time with friends. Some people also try new hobbies or learn new skills because it helps them stay motivated and mentally active.</p>
<p><strong>4. Why are some teachers’ classes boring? Are there any solutions?</strong></p>
<p>I think classes become boring when teachers only focus on theory and don’t interact much with students. If lessons are too repetitive, students may stop paying attention after a while. As for solutions, I think teachers could make classes more engaging by adding discussions, group activities, or practical exercises instead of just lecturing all the time.</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="background-color: #f8cac6; font-size: 14pt;">8 Describe a home that you like to visit but do not want to live in</span></strong></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Where it is</p>
<p>What it is like</p>
<p>Why you like to visit it</p>
<p>And explain why you would not like to live there </p>
<p>Sample:</p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about my cousin’s house, which is a place I really enjoy visiting but probably wouldn’t want to live in permanently.</p>
<p>Her house is located in a small countryside area, about two hours away from my city. It’s a large traditional house with a beautiful garden, and the atmosphere there is really peaceful and relaxing. There are lots of trees, flowers, and open spaces around the house, so it feels very close to nature.</p>
<p>I like visiting it because it’s a perfect place to take a break from busy city life. Whenever I go there, I feel much calmer and less stressed. Usually, I spend time chatting with my cousin, eating home-cooked meals, or just sitting outside enjoying the fresh air. Honestly, it’s the kind of place where you can truly relax.</p>
<p>However, I don’t think I’d like to live there long-term. The main reason is that it’s quite far from the city center, so it’s not very convenient. There aren’t many shopping centers, entertainment places, or public services nearby. Also, I think I’d eventually get bored because the lifestyle there is much quieter and slower than what I’m used to.</p>
<p>So yeah, even though I really enjoy visiting that house occasionally, I still prefer living in a more modern and convenient area.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3:</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Do people in your country like to visit others’ homes?</strong></p>
<p>Yeah, definitely. In my country, visiting other people’s homes is quite common, especially during holidays, birthdays, or special occasions. I mean, it’s considered a good way to maintain relationships and spend time with family or friends.</p>
<p><strong>2. What do people do when they visit others?</strong></p>
<p>Well, people usually chat, eat together, or sometimes bring small gifts like fruit or snacks. If it’s a special occasion, they might also celebrate or have a meal together. Honestly, visiting someone’s house is often more about socializing and enjoying each other’s company.</p>
<p><strong>3. What kind of place do people in your country like to live in?</strong></p>
<p>I think most people prefer living in places that are convenient and comfortable. For example, younger people often like modern apartments in the city because they’re close to work or entertainment areas, while older people may prefer quieter places with more space and greenery.</p>
<p><strong>4. What''s the difference between homes in cities and those in the countryside?</strong></p>
<p>Hmm, there are quite a few differences. Homes in cities are usually smaller and more modern because space is limited and expensive. In contrast, countryside houses tend to be larger and surrounded by nature. Also, life in rural areas is generally quieter and less stressful than in big cities.</p>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: #f8cac6; font-size: 14pt;">9. Describe a person who has chosen a career in the medical field (e.g a doctor, a nurse)</span></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>Who he/she is</p>
<p>What he/she does</p>
<p>Why he/she chose this career</p>
<p>And explain how you feel about him/her</p>
<p><strong>Sample:</strong></p>
<p>Well, I’d like to talk about my cousin, who works as a doctor at a public hospital in my city. She’s someone I really admire because working in the medical field is definitely not an easy job.</p>
<p>She mainly treats patients and gives medical advice. From what she’s told me, her job can be extremely stressful because she sometimes has to work long shifts and deal with emergency cases. But despite that, she still seems very dedicated to her work.</p>
<p>As for why she chose this career, I think it’s because she genuinely wanted to help people. Ever since she was young, she had been interested in biology and healthcare. Also, one of her family members used to have serious health problems, so that experience probably inspired her to become a doctor.</p>
<p>Honestly, I really respect her because she’s hardworking, patient, and responsible. I mean, medical workers play such an important role in society, especially after the pandemic when people became more aware of how difficult their jobs are.</p>
<p>So yeah, whenever I talk to her about her work, I always feel impressed by her dedication and professionalism.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1 Do you think doctors and nurses are very important?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, absolutely. Doctors and nurses play a vital role in maintaining public health. Doctors diagnose illnesses and provide treatment, while nurses ensure patients are cared for and supported during recovery. Without their expertise and dedication, our healthcare system wouldn’t function effectively</p>
<p><strong>2 Who is more important, doctors or nurses?</strong></p>
<p>I think both are equally important, as they have different but complementary roles. Doctors focus on diagnosing and treating patients, while nurses provide essential care and emotional support. Together, they create a team that ensures patients receive the best possible treatment.</p>
<p><strong>3 Do you think that doctors and nurses are not paid enough?</strong></p>
<p>In many countries, doctors and nurses are not paid enough considering the long hours and emotional stress they face. They deal with life-and-death situations and take on significant responsibilities, so I believe their salaries should reflect the importance of their work</p>
<p><strong>4 Do you think it is necessary to learn first aids skills?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, learning first aid skills is crucial because it can save lives in emergencies. For example, knowing how to perform CPR or treat minor injuries can make a big difference before professional help arrives. It’s a skill everyone should have, as accidents can happen at any time</p>
<hr>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt; background-color: #f8cac6;">10 Describe an item on which you spent more than expected </span></strong></p>
<p>You should say:</p>
<p>What it is</p>
<p>How much you spent on it </p>
<p>Why you bought it</p>
<p>And explain why you think you spent more than expected</p>
<p><br><strong>SAMPLE:</strong></p>
<p>Well, the item I want to talk about is a pair of wireless noise-cancelling headphones that I bought last year. I had been thinking about getting a good pair for studying, but honestly, I didn’t plan to spend too much.</p>
<p>At first, I expected to spend around 1 or 1.5 million VND. But after trying several models at the store, I ended up buying a premium one that cost nearly 4 million VND. It was way more than what I had in mind, and I remember standing there for like ten minutes, questioning whether I was making a mistake.</p>
<p>The reason I bought it was because, you know, I really needed something to help me focus. At that time, I was preparing for my IELTS exam, and my neighborhood was quite noisy. When I tested the headphones, the sound quality was amazing, and the noise-cancelling feature blocked out almost everything. I could literally feel the difference.</p>
<p>I think I spent more than expected mainly because I got carried away by the features. Also, the salesperson was really convincing, saying that investing in a high-quality pair would last me much longer. And to be fair, he was right — I use them every day for studying, travelling, and even relaxing.</p>
<p>So even though it was more expensive than I had planned, I don’t regret it at all, because it has made my study routine so much more productive and enjoyable.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Part 3</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Do you often buy more than you expected?</strong></p>
<p>Well, to be honest, yes — sometimes. Especially when I shop online. You know, there are always discounts, recommendations, and “buy 1 get 1” offers, so it’s easy to get carried away. I don’t overspend too much, but I do occasionally buy things that I didn’t originally plan to buy.</p>
<p><strong>2. What do you think young people spend most of their money on?</strong></p>
<p>I think young people today spend a lot on technology, like smartphones, earbuds, and laptops. Besides that, they also spend quite a lot on entertainment — food, fashion, travelling, and even online subscriptions. Many also invest in education, such as language courses or skill training, which is actually a good thing.</p>
<p><strong>3. Do you think it is important to save money? Why?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, definitely. Saving money gives people a sense of security, especially when unexpected situations happen, like medical issues or job loss. It also helps people achieve long-term goals, such as buying a house, studying abroad, or starting a business. Without saving, it’s difficult to feel stable or plan for the future.</p>
<p><strong>4. Do people buy things they don’t need?</strong></p>
<p>Oh yes, absolutely. People often buy unnecessary things because of advertising, trends, or peer pressure. Sometimes they shop just to feel better or relieve stress. Modern shopping apps also make it too easy — with one click, you can buy almost anything. So it’s not surprising that many people end up owning things they rarely use.</p>
